jsession 0.3.0 by Joseph Lansdowne.

A tiny session manager for X.

http://ikn.org.uk/jsession

    LICENSE

Distributed under the terms of the BSD 3-Clause license; if this was not
included, you can find it here:
    https://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-3-Clause

    INSTALLATION

Run `make install'.  The usual `DESTDIR', etc. arguments to `make' are
supported.

    DEPENDENCIES

Bash: http://www.gnu.org/software/bash
GNU grep or equivalent
DBus: http://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/dbus
pm-utils: http://pm-utils.freedesktop.org/wiki/
    optional: suspend support (not required if using systemd)
run-parts (debianutils): http://packages.qa.debian.org/d/debianutils.html
    optional: run executables as root on login
sed: https://www.gnu.org/software/sed/manual/sed.html
    at build-time only

    USAGE

See `jsession --help' and `jsession-quit --help' for details.  Start the daemon
(as root) using the systemd service, or just execute `jsessiond'.
